    Z "Tu culo es adictivo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2150
translate spanish d14b68_194261ea:

    # Asa "Mh... and so are your visits, [persistent.player_name]..."
    Asa "Mh... y también tus visitas, [persistent.player_name]..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2151
translate spanish d14b68_9a3aebd5:

    # Asa "I shall look forward to our next time."
    Asa "Esperaré con ansias nuestra próxima vez."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2162
translate spanish d14b111_24c3c2ad:

    # "Afterwards, you spend some time cleaning up the mess you made, and exchanging flirty nothings."
    "Después, pasáis un rato limpiando el desastre que habéis hecho e intercambiando coqueteos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2163
translate spanish d14b111_56920759:

    # "It's like Asani said... You came here so you could fuck each others' brains out, and spending many words on the deed or on your different lifestyles is pointless, once you are satisfied."
    "Es como dijo Asani... Vinisteis allí para poder follaros a tope, y gastar muchas palabras sobre el hecho o sobre vuestros diferentes estilos de vida no tiene sentido, una vez que estáis satisfechos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2164
translate spanish d14b111_a1cac13d:

    # "Both of you having got what you came for, you resolve to leave, but still can't leave things unsaid."
    "Habiendo conseguido ambos lo que habías venido a buscar, decides marcharte, pero no puedes dejar las cosas sin decir."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2167
translate spanish d14b111_4fc1db44:

    # Z "If you ever leave this place, let me know before you do, ok?"
    Z "Si alguna vez decides dejar este lugar, avísame antes de hacerlo, ¿vale?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2170
translate spanish d14b111_a7194f5f:

    # Asa "Oh, don't concern yourself about that, babe. Not that I intend to move anytime soon."
    Asa "Oh, no te preocupes por eso, nene. No es que tenga intención de mudarme pronto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2175
translate spanish d14b111_158a024c:

    # Z "Remember, Asani. The offer still stands. I can help you get out of here."
    Z "Recuerda, Asani. La oferta sigue en pie. Puedo ayudarte a salir de aquí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2176
translate spanish d14b111_d6947333:

    # Z "Just give me the word."
    Z "Sólo tienes que decírmelo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2179
translate spanish d14b111_73856eb8:

    # Asa "Don't you worry about me, [persistent.player_name]."
    Asa "No te preocupes por mí, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2180
translate spanish d14b111_63d88c44:

    # Asa "I'm not a small girl, I can take care of myself. You will see, next time you visit me."
    Asa "No soy una niña pequeña, puedo cuidarme sola. Ya lo verás, la próxima vez que me visites."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2183
translate spanish d14b111_f359bc43:

    # Z "Alright then..."
    Z "De acuerdo entonces..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2184
translate spanish d14b111_62941acb:

    # Z "Until next time, Asani. And be careful... of who you let inside."
    Z "Hasta la próxima, Asani. Y ten cuidado... de a quién dejas entrar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2187
translate spanish d14b111_219ae969:

    # Asa "..."
    Asa "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2190
translate spanish d14b111_8c1f08fe:

    # "You drive home..."
    "Conduces hasta casa..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2196
translate spanish d14c_d1b0e63a:

    # Z "I am ready to return to Abrax. I need answers."
    Z "Estoy listo para regresar con Abrax. Necesito respuestas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2197
translate spanish d14c_8131d684:

    # Z "And I will get them."
    Z "Y las conseguiré."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2198
translate spanish d14c_7aabc90e:

    # Z "About the glowing object... about the Scorched Earth project. About what my old master is planning."
    Z "Acerca del objeto brillante... acerca del proyecto de Tierra Quemada. Acerca de lo que mi antiguo Maestro está planeando."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2202
translate spanish d14c_524359ba:

    # "Later, somewhere in Old Cairo..."
    "Más tarde, en algún lugar del Viejo Cairo..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2214
translate spanish d14c_23b436be:

    # Dec "Lord Abrax? He is not here."
    Dec "¿Lord Abrax? No está aquí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2215
translate spanish d14c_06ffa1ad:

    # Z "I need to speak to him. I am...-"
    Z "Necesito hablar con él. Soy...-"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2216
translate spanish d14c_353135b6:

    # Dec "I know who you are. He is waiting for you."
    Dec "Sé quién eres. Él te está esperando."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2217
translate spanish d14c_5b6a682c:

    # Dec "But as I said, he is not around."
    Dec "Pero como dije, él no está aquí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2218
translate spanish d14c_87cf9924:

    # Dec "Follow the road back outside. Head to the west. Drive past the red crater, you will see a living area."
    Dec "Sigue el camino de vuelta al exterior. Dirígete hacia el oeste. Pasa el cráter rojo y verás una zona habitada."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2219
translate spanish d14c_cea0dbea:

    # Dec "The Lord spends his time there, contemplating."
    Dec "El Señor pasa su tiempo allí, contemplando."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2220
translate spanish d14c_5ab3574d:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2224
translate spanish d14c_8f425254:

    # "You follow his directions. You drive past a red crater you heard stories about, until you see what remains of an apartment complex."
    "Sigues sus indicaciones. Pasas por delante de un cráter rojo del que habías oído historias, hasta que ves lo que queda de un complejo de apartamentos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2225
translate spanish d14c_bda0fd25:

    # "A long while later, you reach your destination, and finally see figures on the rooftops. Shadows engulfed into an ever darkening red sky."
    "Un buen rato después, llegas a tu destino, y por fin ves figuras en los tejados. Sombras engullidas en un cielo rojo cada vez más oscuro."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2228
translate spanish d14c_daf48c80:

    # "The sea of smog that plagues these lands is deadly. Here however, at the summit of the building, after having climbed many stairs, you find that the cloud lingers beneath you, intangible."
    "El mar de niebla tóxica que asola estas tierras es mortal. Sin embargo, aquí, en la cima del edificio, tras haber subido muchas escaleras, descubres que la nube persiste bajo ti, intangible."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2229
translate spanish d14c_2d238181:

    # "At least, you think, you are prepared. You brought a mask to protect yourself from the smog."
    "Al menos, piensas, estás preparado. Has traído una mascarilla para protegerte de la niebla tóxica."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2230
translate spanish d14c_952d2e13:

    # "But will it protect you from what you are about to learn?"
    "¿Pero te protegerá de lo que estás a punto de conocer?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2233
translate spanish d14c_0191ba01:

    # Z "{i}*heavy breathing*{/i}"
    Z "{i}*respiración agitada*{/i}"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2236
translate spanish d14c_937bd611:

    # "As you turn to your left, familiar shapes are standing on the rooftop before you."
    "Al girarte a la izquierda, ves formas familiares de pie en el tejado frente a ti."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2237
translate spanish d14c_f04b7569:

    # "Decayed, wrapped in loose cloth, wearing a defect hazard mask. You would feel intimidated, had you not seen much, much worse over the years."
    "Descadentes, envueltos en telas sueltas, con una máscara de riesgo de defectos. Te sentirías intimidado, si no hubieras visto cosas mucho, mucho peores a lo largo de los años."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2238
translate spanish d14c_3463d2b9:

    # Dec "We have been hearing of your arrival, Stalker."
    Dec "Nos hemos enterado de tu llegada, Acechador."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2239
translate spanish d14c_8ea4642f:

    # Dec "Lord Abrax is expecting you."
    Dec "Lord Abrax te está esperando."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2242
translate spanish d14c_912110bd:

    # "You climb further, stepping up to them."
    "Sigues subiendo, acercándote a ellos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2245
translate spanish d14c_efaf02fb:

    # Dec "Hand us your weapons and go meet him. Don't let the Lord wait."
    Dec "Dadnos vuestras armas y salid a su encuentro. No dejes que el Señor espere."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2246
translate spanish d14c_e1303be7:

    # Dec "We are watching you, Stalker [persistent.player_name]. No wrong moves."
    Dec "Te estamos observando, Acechador [persistent.player_name]. No des pasos en falso."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2250
translate spanish d14c_af4eafc3:

    # LA "[persistent.player_name]. My old friend."
    LA "[persistent.player_name], mi viejo amigo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2251
translate spanish d14c_d3010c33:

    # LA "Join us."
    LA "Únete a nosotros."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2255
translate spanish d14c_33d5542f:

    # Z "You have a lot to explain."
    Z "Tienes mucho que explicar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2256
translate spanish d14c_7d9eae45:

    # LA "I shall..."
    LA "Lo haré..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2257
translate spanish d14c_c0abcab0:

    # LA "...but it means that your protege was successful, wasn't she?"
    LA "... pero eso significa que tu protegida ha tenido éxito, ¿no?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2260
translate spanish d14c_09b5328e:

    # Z "She did find something, yes."
    Z "Ella ha encontrado algo, sí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2261
translate spanish d14c_ad4382fb:

    # Z "A cylinder made of metal and glass, glowing with ominous light."
    Z "Un cilindro hecho de metal y vidrio, que brilla con una luz ominosa."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2262
translate spanish d14c_46e49ce0:

    # LA "Then she has succeeded in her task. It was not a simple one, either."
    LA "Entonces ha tenido éxito en su tarea. Tampoco era una tarea sencilla."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2263
translate spanish d14c_1b50e80a:

    # LA "She takes after her [persistent.dad]'s success, then."
    LA "Ella sigue el éxito de su [persistent.dad], entonces."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2265
translate spanish d14c_8187cc24:

    # Z "I need to know more about this object."
    Z "Necesito saber más sobre ese objeto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2268
translate spanish d14c_6836a5bc:

    # Z "She found a fair number of things."
    Z "Ella encontró un buen número de cosas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2269
translate spanish d14c_45fd612f:

    # Z "What {i}are{/i} you hoping she found? And what is it worth to you?"
    Z "¿Qué {i}esperas{/i} que haya encontrado? ¿Y cuánto vale para ti?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2270
translate spanish d14c_ab8cf1da:

    # LA "You've learned well to speak with caution, but there is no need to be cagey with me."
    LA "Has aprendido bien a hablar con cautela, pero no hay necesidad de ser cauteloso conmigo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2271
translate spanish d14c_cb4c25b6:

    # Z "I want to know more about what it is that you were after."
    Z "Quiero saber más acerca de lo que buscabas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2275
translate spanish d14c_af7a42d1:

    # Z "I am afraid she was not."
    Z "Me temo que no."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2276
translate spanish d14c_9e9f6b3a:

    # LA "..."
    LA "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2277
translate spanish d14c_a5a6c70a:

    # LA "Is that so? Maybe I overestimated her abilities..."
    LA "¿En serio? Tal vez sobreestimé sus habilidades..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2278
translate spanish d14c_d540c149:

    # LA "Nevertheless, there are different paths that lead us to the goal we want to achieve."
    LA "Sin embargo, hay diferentes caminos que nos conducen a la meta que queremos alcanzar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2280
translate spanish d14c_60afa966:

    # LA "There is always a different way... and everything, and everyone, can be replaced."
    LA "Siempre hay una forma diferente... y todo, y todos, pueden ser sustituidos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2284
translate spanish d14c_af87d5a4:

    # LA "The object that your pupil was tasked to find is centuries old, [persistent.player_name]."
    LA "El objeto que tu pupila debía encontrar tiene siglos de antigüedad, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2286
translate spanish d14c_64b2386c:

    # LA "As for its purpose...You will understand it in due time."
    LA "En cuanto a su propósito... lo entenderás a su debido tiempo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2289
translate spanish d14c_fc319cff:

    # LA "The first journey through an emission intensive Zone can be life changing, and life ending."
    LA "El primer viaje a través de una Zona de emisión intensiva puede cambiarte la vida, y acabar con ella."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2290
translate spanish d14c_d2fcabb8:

    # LA "I congratulate your [persistent.da] on her success. She takes after you, so it seems."
    LA "Felicito a tu [persistent.da] por su éxito. Al parecer, se parece a ti."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2293
translate spanish d14c_68b6fa6f:

    # LA "Anyway, you came seeking answers, and I did promise I will provide them..."
    LA "De todos modos, viniste en busca de respuestas, y prometí que las proporcionaría..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2294
translate spanish d14c_272b262f:

    # LA "But first...."
    LA "Pero primero...."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2300
translate spanish d14c_6a3d4609:

    # LA "Take a good look at the city, [persistent.player_name]."
    LA "Echa un buen vistazo a la ciudad, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2301
translate spanish d14c_a25d183e:

    # LA "What do you see?"
    LA "¿Qué ves?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2306
translate spanish d14c_1c38fdb8:

    # Z "The remains of a dead civilization long gone."
    Z "Los restos de una civilización muerta desaparecida hace tiempo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2307
translate spanish d14c_c1b28304:

    # Z "All its advances, innovation and progress, lost with it."
    Z "Todos sus avances, innovación y progreso, se perdieron con ello."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2309
translate spanish d14c_0ad38c7f:

    # LA "As seen through the lens of whom?"
    LA "Visto desde la perspectiva de quién."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2310
translate spanish d14c_86371ff5:

    # LA "A citizen of the great desert city of Zeta, who's only contact with the outside world are caravans and the occasional emissions coming from these very ruins?"
    LA "Un ciudadano de la gran ciudad desértica de Zeta, cuyo único contacto con el mundo exterior son las caravanas y las emisiones ocasionales que provienen de estas ruinas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2311
translate spanish d14c_e545b59e:

    # LA "Or seen through the lens of a man who travelled the lands, who has seen the impact and magnitude of what was lost?"
    LA "¿O vistas a través de la lente de un hombre que recorrió las tierras, que ha visto el impacto y la magnitud de lo que se perdió?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2312
translate spanish d14c_21363597:

    # LA "A civilization gone for centuries... yes."
    LA "Una civilización desaparecida hace siglos... sí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2314
translate spanish d14c_7c4536a1:

    # LA "Gone forever... no."
    LA "Se ha ido para siempre... no."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2319
translate spanish d14c_cfa59676:

    # Z "Cairo's mist is spreading unusually far outside the city."
    Z "La niebla del Cairo se está extendiendo inusualmente fuera de la ciudad."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2320
translate spanish d14c_49e0cb53:

    # Z "And those emissions... they're rolling further out."
    Z "Y esas emisiones... se están extendiendo aún más."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2322
translate spanish d14c_53f8865d:

    # LA "They are indeed."
    LA "En efecto, lo están."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2326
translate spanish d14c_dceaeb83:

    # Z "Possibilites, secrets and hidden treasures."
    Z "Posibilidades, secretos y tesoros ocultos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2327
translate spanish d14c_4f0e9a8a:

    # Z "But the remains of this city are too dangerous in some parts for even the most prepared adventurers."
    Z "Pero los restos de esta ciudad son demasiado peligrosos en algunas partes incluso para los aventureros más preparados."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2328
translate spanish d14c_892fc798:

    # LA "And secrets of value beyond anything that we could understand."
    LA "Y secretos de valor más allá de lo que podríamos entender."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2329
translate spanish d14c_7818bcdf:

    # LA "I taught you to be curious of the unknown."
    LA "Te enseñé a ser curioso acerca de lo desconocido."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2330
translate spanish d14c_324886c3:

    # LA "And... you listened."
    LA "Y... escuchaste."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2336
translate spanish d14c24_25a82648:

    # LA "Ruins like these are a curse to the living, [persistent.player_name]."
    LA "Ruinas como éstas son una maldición para los vivos, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2337
translate spanish d14c24_22175515:

    # LA "For hundreds of years, we are told, the mist has been spreading from cities like this one."
    LA "Durante cientos de años, nos dicen, la niebla se ha ido extendiendo desde ciudades como ésta."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2340
translate spanish d14c24_c4a1ca3e:

    # LA "But the poisonous dust and smog... it never reaches far outside of them."
    LA "Pero el polvo venenoso y el smog... nunca llegan lejos fuera de ellas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2341
translate spanish d14c24_866ca094:

    # LA "Living beings that make it inside the city are doomed to vanish, or... in the case of the decayed, change forever."
    LA "Los seres vivos que consiguen entrar en la ciudad están condenados a desaparecer, o... en el caso de los descompuestos, a cambiar para siempre."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2344
translate spanish d14c24_9d737e1d:

    # Z "And they cease to be human."
    Z "Y dejan de ser humanos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2345
translate spanish d14c24_0e421e70:

    # Z "Cannibals, men and women who lose their morals, their ability to procreate, and who hunt people for food."
    Z "Caníbales, hombres y mujeres que pierden la moral, la capacidad de procrear y que cazan personas para alimentarse."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2346
translate spanish d14c24_935b925c:

    # Z "And now, my old Master Zosar has become their leader."
    Z "Y ahora, mi antiguo Maestro Zosar se ha convertido en su líder."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2347
translate spanish d14c24_a60dafed:

    # Z "Help me make sense of it. I am not one of your students anymore. Who have you become to betray your own ways?"
    Z "Ayúdame a entenderlo. Ya no soy uno de tus alumnos. ¿En quién te has convertido para traicionar tus propios caminos?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2348
translate spanish d14c24_9e9f6b3a:

    # LA "..."
    LA "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2351
translate spanish d14c24_6f4c2422:

    # LA "Wife... leave us."
    LA "Esposa... déjanos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2354
translate spanish d14c24_ad63b803:

    # Abrw "..."
    Abrw "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2357
translate spanish d14c24_9ef47b15:

    # Abrw "Yes, my Lord."
    Abrw "Sí, mi Señor."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2360
translate spanish d14c24_11249f17:

    # "She walks away, her head low..."
    "Se aleja, con la cabeza gacha..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2363
translate spanish d14c24_5d4d5bf5:

    # LA "I betrayed no one's ways or morals, [persistent.player_name]. Certainly not the ones I taught you all those years ago."
    LA "No traicioné las formas o moral de nadie, [persistent.player_name]. Ciertamente no las que te enseñé todos esos años atrás."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2364
translate spanish d14c24_0a56d80d:

    # LA "The path of a Desert Stalker is to be open to the unknown. The Long Walk I took served this exact purpose."
    LA "El camino de un Acechador del Desierto consiste en estar abierto a lo desconocido. La Larga Marcha que emprendí sirvió exactamente para esto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2370
translate spanish d14c24_73798220:

    # LA "No... what I have discovered, is a truth broader than what the explorers and founders of Zeta laid down for us in their codexes and laws."
    LA "No... lo que he descubierto, es una verdad más amplia que lo que los exploradores y fundadores de Zeta de antaño nos establecieron en sus códices y leyes."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2371
translate spanish d14c24_3c75c20c:

    # LA "You judge and denounce the ways in which the people of Old Cairo provide for themselves, even as you know that its soil is barren, dead."
    LA "Juzgas y denuncias las formas en que la gente del Viejo Cairo se mantiene a sí misma, aun sabiendo que su suelo es estéril, muerto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2374
translate spanish d14c24_48bf3bda:

    # Z "People of Cairo? Everything about the decayed, your people, is unsustainable."
    Z "¿La gente de El Cairo? Todo lo que respecta a los decaídos, tu gente, es insostenible."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2375
translate spanish d14c24_2721cabe:

    # Z "Have you looked at yourself, Master...? You have become a living corpse, a shadow of what you once were."
    Z "¿Te has mirado a ti mismo, Maestro...? Te has convertido en un cadáver viviente, una sombra de lo que una vez fuiste."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2378
translate spanish d14c24_7558c971:

    # LA "And you are right, in a way."
    LA "Y tienes razón, en cierto sentido."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2381
translate spanish d14c24_0e4f2bdf:

    # LA "We are the undead people in a dead world. We are not creating a new civilization, but rediscovering the dead and forgotten one, the one our forefathers have turned their backs on."
    LA "Somos muertos vivientes en un mundo muerto. No estamos creando una nueva civilización, sino redescubriendo la muerta y olvidada, aquella a la que nuestros antepasados dieron la espalda."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2382
translate spanish d14c24_cf66d57b:

    # LA "And that, [persistent.player_name], was my Long Walk. To go where no living man ever went before. To find the reason why things are the way they are."
    LA "Y eso, [persistent.player_name], fue mi Largo Camino. Ir a donde ningún hombre vivo había ido antes. Para encontrar la razón por la que las cosas son como son."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2383
translate spanish d14c24_248b47a9:

    # LA "But I presume you did not come here to argue about our ways."
    LA "Pero supongo que no has venido aquí para discutir sobre nuestras costumbres."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2384
translate spanish d14c24_ab2b99c8:

    # LA "Let me ask you something [persistent.player_name]..."
    LA "Déjame preguntarte algo [persistent.player_name]..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2385
translate spanish d14c24_e719f2b3:

    # LA "Have you ever wondered why the mist largely remains in close proximity of the city? Surely you have been close to the outskirts often enough to observe that the mist is continuously building up."
    LA "¿Te has preguntado alguna vez por qué la niebla permanece en gran medida en las proximidades de la ciudad? Seguro que has estado cerca de las afueras con la suficiente frecuencia como para observar que la niebla se acumula continuamente."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2388
translate spanish d14c24_bf29840e:

    # Z "I have noticed that, yes, but it's one of those things that just are... I guess that the Holy Storms happen often enough to prevent the mist from expanding too much."
    Z "Lo he notado, sí, pero es una de esas cosas que simplemente son... Supongo que las Tormentas Sagradas ocurren lo suficiente como para evitar que la niebla se expanda demasiado."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2391
translate spanish d14c24_76ebff78:

    # LA "Yes, but why is that?"
    LA "Sí, pero ¿por qué?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2394
translate spanish d14c24_1e9c27d7:

    # Z "It just is. Why does the Sun burn our skin and heat the sand of the desert? Why do birds fly?"
    Z "Simplemente es así. ¿Por qué el Sol quema nuestra piel y calienta la arena del desierto? ¿Por qué vuelan los pájaros?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2397
translate spanish d14c24_b27e9438:

    # LA "Precisely. Natural phenomena tend to be accepted and discarded. A storm is coming, because it is coming."
    LA "Precisamente. Los fenómenos naturales tienden a aceptarse y descartarse. Se avecina una tormenta, porque se avecina."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2398
translate spanish d14c24_108c5971:

    # LA "The area around Cairo is uninhabitable, because it has always been like that. The red mist is what it is, and we are lucky that the storms slow it down."
    LA "La zona que rodea El Cairo es inhabitable, porque siempre ha sido así. La niebla roja es lo que es, y tenemos suerte de que las tormentas la ralenticen."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2401
translate spanish d14c24_c50bf6b1:

    # LA "In fact, that's why we started calling them Holy Storms in the first place."
    LA "De hecho, por eso empezamos a llamarlas Tormentas Sagradas en primer lugar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2402
translate spanish d14c24_da98b8bf:

    # LA "Such is the human condition. When something becomes a daily occurrence, we blame the gods, find shelter, make do and move on."
    LA "Así es la condición humana. Cuando algo se convierte en cotidiano, echamos la culpa a los dioses, buscamos refugio, nos arreglamos y seguimos adelante."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2404
translate spanish d14c24_a9755a67:

    # LA "For decades, centuries, we have been told the lie that we should accept things as they are because we cannot pierce the veil of what is unknown."
    LA "Durante décadas, siglos, nos han contado la mentira de que debemos aceptar las cosas como son porque no podemos traspasar el velo de lo desconocido."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2405
translate spanish d14c24_9af15197:

    # LA "A lie concocted because our ancestors who caused the End of Days couldn't own up to their mistakes."
    LA "Una mentira tramada porque nuestros antepasados, quienes causaron el fin de los días, no pudieron asumir sus errores."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2406
translate spanish d14c24_fe4d648f:

    # LA "So we rebuilt a dream, the vision of a few broken minds who salvaged what they could and tried to build a world according to what they thought of as a happier, and simpler, time."
    LA "Así que reconstruimos un sueño, la visión de unas cuantas mentes rotas que rescataron lo que pudieron e intentaron construir un mundo de acuerdo con lo que consideraban una época más feliz y sencilla."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2407
translate spanish d14c24_269a9d4e:

    # LA "Most importantly, we were told that it is what it is and we cannot, {i}should not{/i} change anything."
    LA "Y lo más importante, nos dijeron que es lo que es y que no podemos, {i}no debemos{/i} cambiar nada."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2408
translate spanish d14c24_6453bbfb:

    # LA "Technology, knowledge, the old ways were vilified. We are told to not repeat the mistakes of the past again."
    LA "Se denigró la tecnología, el conocimiento, las viejas costumbres. Se nos dice que no volvamos a repetir los errores del pasado."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2409
translate spanish d14c24_2671c466:

    # LA "But I have discovered the reason why things are the way they are... and finding out demanded an enormous sacrifice."
    LA "Pero he descubierto la razón por la que las cosas son como son... y averiguarlo exigió un enorme sacrificio."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2412
translate spanish d14c24_07811ffa:

    # LA "A sacrifice greater than my own self."
    LA "Un sacrificio mayor que mi propio ser."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2413
translate spanish d14c24_bd720b74:

    # LA "But now I understand more..."
    LA "Pero ahora entiendo más..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2416
translate spanish d14c24_3f5f41b5:

    # LA "...about the scorched earth we are standing on."
    LA "... sobre la tierra calcinada que estamos pisando."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2425
translate spanish d14c24_9287f8ee:

    # LA "Look up, old friend. It is starting..."
    LA "Mira hacia arriba, viejo amigo. Está empezando..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2432
translate spanish d14c24_36ea3131:

    # LA "What we are witnessing right now, [persistent.player_name]... is not nature following the rules of a post-apocalyptic world."
    LA "Lo que estamos presenciando ahora mismo, [persistent.player_name]... no es la naturaleza siguiendo las reglas de un mundo postapocalíptico."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2437
translate spanish d14c24_ae33dd6b:

    # Z "A Holy Storm... the mist is fading away."
    Z "Una Tormenta Sagrada... la niebla se desvanece."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2440
translate spanish d14c24_6ea10b5d:

    # LA "It did not fade away. It was repressed."
    LA "No se desvaneció. Se reprimió."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2446
translate spanish d14c24_0f4e378b:

    # LA "Nothing you are seeing is natural. Neither the storm itself, nor the red mist."
    LA "Nada de lo que ves es natural. Ni la tormenta en sí, ni la niebla roja."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2447
translate spanish d14c24_039f71a0:

    # LA "Those so-called Holy Storms of yours, are neither holy, nor divine, no matter what the Temple teaches and would like for your people to believe otherwise."
    LA "Esas supuestas Tormentas Sagradas vuestras, no son ni sagradas, ni divinas, por mucho que el Templo enseñe y quiera que tu pueblo crea lo contrario."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2448
translate spanish d14c24_e58ca302:

    # LA "No, they are the product of a relic... of times long past, from before the End of Days, named after an Egyptian god of the sun and sky."
    LA "No, son producto de una reliquia... de tiempos pasados, de antes del Fin de los Días, que lleva el nombre de un dios egipcio del sol y del cielo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2449
translate spanish d14c24_316582c0:

    # Zt "The Horus system..."
    Zt "El sistema Horus..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2450
translate spanish d14c24_baac5cc6:

    # Z "How can something like this... last for centuries."
    Z "Cómo puede algo así... durar siglos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2451
translate spanish d14c24_42e09e30:

    # LA "There are many relics of the old world out there, you should know that better than most."
    LA "Hay muchas reliquias del viejo mundo ahí fuera, deberías saberlo mejor que la mayoría."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2452
translate spanish d14c24_7596069d:

    # LA "Relics they may be, but they can still have an influence over our world, they {i}do{/i} still influence our world."
    LA "Puede que sean reliquias, pero aún pueden influir en nuestro mundo, {i}todavía{/i} influyen en nuestro mundo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2454
translate spanish d14c24_33c1cb87:

    # LA "You have seen the artifact. You have held it in your hands. You have felt the undying energy it radiates."
    LA "Has visto el artefacto. Lo has tenido en tus manos. Has sentido la energía imperecedera que irradia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2456
translate spanish d14c24_3c416cff:

    # LA "It's unfortunate that your pupil never found the object. If she had, you would have touched it with your hand, experience for yourself the energy it radiates."
    LA "Es una pena que tu pupila no encontrara el objeto. Si lo hubiera hecho, lo habrías tocado con la mano, habrías experimentado por ti mismo la energía que irradia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2457
translate spanish d14c24_5ab3574d:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2458
translate spanish d14c24_e90c7e06:

    # Z "A power source..."
    Z "Una fuente de energía..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2459
translate spanish d14c24_36f80fa5:

    # "You stay silent. The notion of a system to control the storms perturbs you..."
    "Permaneces en silencio. La idea de un sistema para controlar las tormentas te perturba..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2461
translate spanish d14c24_285f5f04:

    # LA "When the right time comes, we may once again gain control over those relics our ancestors left behind."
    LA "Cuando llegue el momento adecuado, podremos volver a controlar esas reliquias que dejaron nuestros antepasados."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2462
translate spanish d14c24_31b0f4e3:

    # LA "We will put an end to what denies us access to our lost civilization... to the unnecessary wars we fight, and to the scarcity that rules over this world."
    LA "Pondremos fin a lo que nos niega el acceso a nuestra civilización perdida... a las guerras innecesarias que libramos y a la escasez que domina este mundo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2463
translate spanish d14c24_5ab3574d_1:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2465
translate spanish d14c24_9a2513e6:

    # LA "[persistent.player_name], you are standing at a crossroads."
    LA "[persistent.player_name], te encuentras en una encrucijada."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2467
translate spanish d14c24_676a82e0:

    # LA "I invite you to visit me again soon."
    LA "Te invito a que vuelvas a visitarme pronto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2471
translate spanish d14c24_ea81ffce:

    # Z "Why would I..."
    Z "¿Por qué iba a...?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2472
translate spanish d14c24_514f3eb7:

    # LA "To learn. To observe, and not merely judge from a safe distance."
    LA "Para aprender. Para observar y no sólo juzgar desde una distancia segura."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2473
translate spanish d14c24_bbc6e8e3:

    # Z "Your ways make it difficult, old Master."
    Z "Tus maneras lo hacen difícil, viejo Maestro."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2474
translate spanish d14c24_859d1414:

    # LA "Judgement. Disgust, even. Yet you are not above taking advantage of my people's labour and goods for years."
    LA "Juicio. Incluso repugnancia. Sin embargo, no dejas de aprovecharte del trabajo y los bienes de mi pueblo durante años."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2475
translate spanish d14c24_6bc15b11:

    # LA "Be that as it may, I believe that you will keep an open mind."
    LA "Sea como fuere, creo que mantendrás la mente abierta."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2476
translate spanish d14c24_5ab3574d_2:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2479
translate spanish d14c24_f6b61606:

    # Z "I could tell the Palace about this."
    Z "Podría informar al Palacio sobre esto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2480
translate spanish d14c24_b999d0be:

    # LA "You are welcome to do so."
    LA "Eres bienvenido a hacerlo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2481
translate spanish d14c24_6504a990:

    # LA "Maybe the Queen believes you."
    LA "Quizá la Reina te crea."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2482
translate spanish d14c24_f039e46e:

    # LA "Or maybe years of indoctrination will make her dismiss your claims as fairytales."
    LA "O tal vez años de adoctrinamiento hagan que desestime tus afirmaciones como cuentos de hadas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2484
translate spanish d14c24_2e23720b:

    # LA "What will you confront her with? Will you show her a device whose purpose and physical destination are unknown to you? An item she is most likely going to confiscate?"
    LA "¿Con qué te enfrentarás a ella? ¿Le mostrarás un artefacto cuya finalidad y destino físico desconoces? ¿Un objeto que muy probablemente ella confiscará?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2485
translate spanish d14c24_16634b84:

    # LA "And should your Elders find out you possess ancient technology... people have been branded as traitors for less."
    LA "Y si tus Ancianos descubren que posees tecnología antigua... han marcado a personas como traidoras por mucho menos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2487
translate spanish d14c24_585c083a:

    # LA "And what will you confront her with? The unconfirmed rumor about an object that you don't possess, that is somehow tied to a machine from the past that you don't know where to find?"
    LA "¿Y con qué la enfrentarás? ¿El rumor no confirmado sobre un objeto que no posees, que de alguna manera está relacionado con una máquina del pasado que no sabes dónde encontrar?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2488
translate spanish d14c24_5ab3574d_3:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2490
translate spanish d14c24_33672645:

    # LA "The knowledge I imparted on you is not something that can be shared with just anyone lightly."
    LA "El conocimiento que te impartí no es algo que pueda compartirse con cualquiera a la ligera."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2491
translate spanish d14c24_711f8b93:

    # LA "You can walk away if you want. But doing so will preclude you any further understanding of what you have learned today."
    LA "Puedes alejarte si quieres. Pero hacerlo te impedirá seguir comprendiendo lo que has aprendido hoy."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2492
translate spanish d14c24_c3fee989:

    # LA "You will not help the cause of the decayed by seeing their way, nor will you help your Queen's cause by being ignorant of it, either."
    LA "No ayudarás a la causa de los decaídos viendo su camino, ni tampoco ayudarás a la causa de tu Reina ignorándolo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2494
translate spanish d14c24_36553531:

    # LA "I have said enough, [persistent.player_name]. I will await your return."
    LA "He dicho suficiente, [persistent.player_name]. Esperaré tu regreso."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2496
translate spanish d14c24_203c8be1:

    # "As you stand there, together on the edge of a crumbling building, you consider your options and what to make of the revelations of this day."
    "Mientras permaneces allí, juntos al borde de un edificio en ruinas, consideras tus opciones y qué hacer con las revelaciones de este día."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2500
translate spanish d14c24_58c37662:

    # "What do they mean for Zeta? And what do you make of your former master's intentions? How much of what he told you is truth, and how much of his true intentions has he yet to reveal?"
    "¿Qué significan para Zeta? ¿Y qué opinas de las intenciones de tu antiguo Maestro? ¿Cuánto de lo que te dijo es verdad, y cuánto de sus verdaderas intenciones aún no ha revelado?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2501
translate spanish d14c24_0689a1ac:

    # "His silence confirms to you that this audience has come to an end. You almost smile, as your mind goes to countless lessons of the past that would end just as abruptly and unceremoniously."
    "Su silencio te confirma que esta audiencia ha llegado a su fin. Casi sonríes, mientras tu mente se remonta a innumerables lecciones del pasado que terminaban de forma igual de abrupta y poco ceremoniosa."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2502
translate spanish d14c24_c15661e8:

    # "You take a few steps back, without saying a word to Lord Abrax, who seems lost in thought, before turning around towards the stairs, ready to leave this place."
    "Retrocedes unos pasos, sin decir palabra a Lord Abrax, que parece ensimismado, antes de darte la vuelta hacia las escaleras, dispuesto a abandonar ese lugar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2520
translate spanish d14d_643494f8:

    # G "My Queen... Stalker [persistent.player_name] enters the temple."
    G "Mi Reina... Acechador [persistent.player_name] entra en el templo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2521
translate spanish d14d_5427b6fd:

    # Q "Let him through."
    Q "Déjale pasar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2524
translate spanish d14d_09414c9c:

    # Q "Hello again, [persistent.player_name]. Give me one second."
    Q "Hola de nuevo, [persistent.player_name]. Dame un segundo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2527
translate spanish d14d_1cb3e321:

    # Q "You two can leave."
    Q "Podéis marcharos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2530
translate spanish d14d_1300589c:

    # Q "I'm glad you considered my proposal, there is work waiting for us."
    Q "Me alegro de que hayas considerado mi propuesta, hay trabajo esperándonos."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2536
translate spanish d14d_a3ad514e:

    # Q "Although..."
    Q "Aunque..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2539
translate spanish d14d_a792608d:

    # Q "I know a place that is better suited for more... strategic discussions."
    Q "Sé de un lugar más adecuado para discusiones más... estratégicas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2540
translate spanish d14d_f4997e2f:

    # Q "It's best we speak somewhere more private."
    Q "Es mejor que hablemos en un lugar más privado."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2543
translate spanish d14d_c4c00724:

    # Z "Alright then... lead the way."
    Z "Muy bien, entonces... ve delante."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2546
translate spanish d14d_7773283b:

    # Q "Follow me."
    Q "Sígueme."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2551
translate spanish d14d_a2bd539b:

    # Q "Listen, [persistent.player_name]..."
    Q "Escucha, [persistent.player_name]..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2552
translate spanish d14d_5ec3a6f0:

    # Q "Before you start, I have to make something clear."
    Q "Antes de que empieces, tengo que aclararte algo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2555
translate spanish d14d_1eca9d61:

    # Q "What happened last time, cannot be repeated."
    Q "Lo que ocurrió la última vez no puede repetirse."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2558
translate spanish d14d_cf5b6e1e:

    # Z "I didn't expect such a change of tone."
    Z "No esperaba un cambio de tono tan grande."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2561
translate spanish d14d_750bcb7a:

    # Q "What happened between your [persistent.da], you and me was an exception."
    Q "Lo que ocurrió entre tu [persistent.da], tú y yo fue una excepción."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2562
translate spanish d14d_329f0c9b:

    # Q "You lured me into a behaviour I can under no circumstances display to any of my temple staff, let alone the public."
    Q "Me has atraído a un comportamiento que no puedo mostrar bajo ningún concepto a nadie de mi personal del templo, y mucho menos al público."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2565
translate spanish d14d_c7433aed:

    # Z "But... you enjoyed it, right?"
    Z "Pero... lo disfrutaste, ¿verdad?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2566
translate spanish d14d_1bff9e28:

    # Z "It's not like I forced you to participate."
    Z "No es que te haya obligado a participar."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2569
translate spanish d14d_f248fe66:

    # Q "You did not... and I never... claimed otherwise..."
    Q "Tú no... y yo nunca... afirmé lo contrario..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2570
translate spanish d14d_90861e72:

    # Q "That is not the point in the first place..."
    Q "En primer lugar, ése no es el objetivo..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2573
translate spanish d14d_fd5d87f8:

    # Z "I understand very well what you want to tell me. This is about control."
    Z "Entiendo perfectamente a dónde quieres llegar. Esto es una cuestión de control."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2576
translate spanish d14d_c55c27a2:

    # Z "You are the Queen, after all. The Elders, and yourself, have created an image of a pure, uncorrupted, and yet fierce Queen."
    Z "Al fin y al cabo, eres la Reina. Los Ancianos, y tú misma, habéis creado la imagen de una Reina pura, incorrupta y, sin embargo, feroz."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2577
translate spanish d14d_919898c8:

    # Z "You cannot be seen having a moment of weakness, not being in control in any circumstance, however intimate."
    Z "No se te puede ver tener un momento de debilidad, no tener el control en ninguna circunstancia, por íntima que sea."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2580
translate spanish d14d_c54c2c92:

    # Z "Your secrets are safe with me, always."
    Z "Tus secretos están a salvo conmigo, siempre."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2583
translate spanish d14d_941c1588:

    # Q "It is still important to me to hear that we understand each other, [persistent.player_name]."
    Q "Sigue siendo importante para mí oír que nos entendemos, [persistent.player_name]."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2584
translate spanish d14d_159a9bb4:

    # Q "...important to hear it from your voice, that you would not put yourself and me by extention, in danger."
    Q "... importante oírlo de tu voz, que no te pondrías a ti mismo y a mí por extensión, en peligro."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2587
translate spanish d14d_c72edceb:

    # Z "And so you did. As for these matters, your secret is safe with my indifference."
    Z "Y así lo hiciste. En cuanto a estos asuntos, tu secreto está a salvo con mi indiferencia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2588
translate spanish d14d_4f589e68:

    # Z "I do not care to let the world know the shape of the Queen's quiver in her lip."
    Z "No me importa que el mundo sepa cómo le tiembla el labio a la Reina."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2589
translate spanish d14d_bdf0bcc7:

    # Z "And if I did, I stand to lose so much more than just my life for doing so. You can trust my survival instincts."
    Z "Y si lo hiciera, me arriesgo a perder mucho más que la vida. Puedes confiar en mis instintos de supervivencia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2592
translate spanish d14d_c97042fa:

    # Q "I guess that is true..."
    Q "Supongo que eso es cierto..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2595
translate spanish d14d_41bf2987:

    # Q "But be warned, Stalker. You are not irreplaceable... Do not presume too much."
    Q "Pero ten cuidado, Acechador. No eres insustituible... No presumas demasiado."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2598
translate spanish d14d_c6a4e4f1:

    # Q "It would be a pity to have to... demote you and your family."
    Q "Sería una pena tener que... degradaros a ti y a tu familia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2602
translate spanish d14d_8e7d5752:

    # Zt "She seems to be surprised at what she just said. It was less of a threat, and more of a warning."
    Zt "Parece sorprendida por lo que acaba de decir. No era tanto una amenaza como una advertencia."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2603
translate spanish d14d_3c1751b2:

    # Zt "She must be concerned about her image. Giving me such a stark warning was something she did not want to do."
    Zt "Debe de estar preocupada por su imagen. No quería hacerme una advertencia tan dura."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2605
translate spanish d14d_0a18d59d:

    # Zt "A sweet attempt to regain control. Her expression shows that she did not mean anything of what she just said."
    Zt "Un dulce intento de recuperar el control. Su expresión muestra que no quiso decir nada de lo que acaba de decir."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2606
translate spanish d14d_a53860c0:

    # Zt "However, she is concerned about her image, which I understand."
    Zt "Sin embargo, está preocupada por su imagen, lo cual comprendo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2609
translate spanish d14d_7d471fc8:

    # Sh "My Queen? I have been given notice of the Stalker's visit. Is he with you?"
    Sh "¿Mi Reina? Me han avisado de la visita del Acechador. ¿Está contigo?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2612
translate spanish d14d_32124cf2:

    # Q "One moment, Sharifa..."
    Q "Un momento, Sharifa..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2613
translate spanish d14d_7c946b7e:

    # Q "I am on my way."
    Q "Estoy en camino."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2617
translate spanish d14d_ac235e30:

    # "She walks towards the door, flashing a brief smile..."
    "Camina hacia la puerta, esbozando una breve sonrisa..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2620
translate spanish d14d_bdc61a01:

    # Q "..."
    Q "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2623
translate spanish d14d_d650b7ab:

    # "She smiles, reassured..."
    "Ella sonríe, tranquilizada..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2626
translate spanish d14d_c98de89c:

    # "...and places her hand on your chest..."
    "... y te pone la mano en el pecho..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2629
translate spanish d14d_5ab3574d:

    # Z "..."
    Z "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2635
translate spanish d14d_bdc61a01_1:

    # Q "..."
    Q "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2636
translate spanish d14d_5c1c5ca3:

    # Sh "My Queen?"
    Sh "¿Mi Reina?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2644
translate spanish d14d_5c8091b5:

    # "She walks towards the door, looking at you, something of a sour expression on her face..."
    "Se dirige hacia la puerta, mirándote, con una expresión algo amarga en la cara..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2649
translate spanish d14d_0e325e82:

    # "A private audience without taking a better look at the Queen?"
    "¿Una audiencia privada sin ver mejor a la Reina?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2655
translate spanish d14d_bdc61a01_2:

    # Q "..."
    Q "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2656
translate spanish d14d_b61096b1:

    # "That stare, it has become familiar to you..."
    "Esa mirada, se te ha hecho familiar..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2662
translate spanish d14d_0f1944c8:

    # Q "...!"
    Q "¡...!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2665
translate spanish d14d_8985017e:

    # "She looks at you, only marginally surprised..."
    "Ella te mira, sólo ligeramente sorprendida..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2668
translate spanish d14d_5e216356:

    # Qw "[persistent.player_name]..."
    Qw "[persistent.player_name]..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2671
translate spanish d14d_bdc61a01_3:

    # Q "..."
    Q "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2677
translate spanish d14d_113974a2:

    # Qw "Stop it..."
    Qw "Basta..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2678
translate spanish d14d_f82911ae:

    # "That was not a convincing retort..."
    "No ha sido una réplica convincente..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2688
translate spanish d14d42_630e062c:

    # Sh "My Queen, I am here for you."
    Sh "Mi Reina, estoy aquí para ti."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2689
translate spanish d14d42_01ca92a5:

    # Sh "It is inappropriate for a mere soldier to enter your private chambers without a chaperone..."
    Sh "No es apropiado que un simple soldado entre en tus aposentos privados sin un acompañante..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2692
translate spanish d14d42_b4f4fae7:

    # Q "{i}*sigh*{/i} Sharifa..."
    Q "{i}*suspiro*{/i} Sharifa..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2695
translate spanish d14d42_e21c0b2d:

    # Q "Stalker [persistent.player_name] has almost sacrificed his [persistent.da]'s life for me, don't you think he deserves a little trust?"
    Q "El Acechador [persistent.player_name] casi ha sacrificado la vida de su [persistent.da] por mí, ¿no crees que merece un poco de confianza?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2696
translate spanish d14d42_fceb3a08:

    # Q "Or do you think you are the only one who deserves a private audience... Sharifa?"
    Q "O crees que eres la única que merece una audiencia privada... ¿Sharifa?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2697
translate spanish d14d42_c081c890:

    # Q "Do I need to remind you of the privileges you enjoy, compared to other guards?"
    Q "¿Necesito recordarte los privilegios de los que disfrutas, en comparación con otros guardias?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2700
translate spanish d14d42_1dd08e60:

    # Sh "No... my Queen. I apologize. I just think that..-"
    Sh "No... mi Reina. Te pido disculpas. Es que creo que..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2703
translate spanish d14d42_7546fa94:

    # Q "[persistent.player_name], follow me into the throne room. We will further discuss the tasks I told you about."
    Q "[persistent.player_name], sígueme a la sala del trono. Seguiremos discutiendo las tareas de las que te he hablado."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2707
translate spanish d14d42_4d894140:

    # "Interrupting her personal guard's subdued manifestation of jealousy, you follow the Queen into her throne room."
    "Interrumpiendo la manifestación de celos contenidos de sus guardias personales, sigues a la Reina hacia su sala del trono."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2720
translate spanish d14e_bb4b6e7e:

    # Ky "Look who's here."
    Ky "Mira quién está aquí."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2727
translate spanish d14e_3b8d5408:

    # Ky "Hey [persistent.player_name], I've seen you driving by."
    Ky "Ey [persistent.player_name], te he visto pasar en coche."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2728
translate spanish d14e_7e3c6fa2:

    # Ky "Before you sit down, I've got a favor to ask you."
    Ky "Antes de que te sientes, tengo que pedirte una cosa."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2735
translate spanish d14e_a279f76b:

    # Z "What could that be..."
    Z "¿Qué quiere que sea...?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2742
translate spanish d14e_772bb7ab:

    # As "Hey boss."
    As "Ey jefe."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2749
translate spanish d14e_05c668e5:

    # Z "What's up, kid."
    Z "¿Qué pasa, pequeña?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2756
translate spanish d14e_c7cf8dc3:

    # Ky "We've been busy shaping up this place. The guys from the towers have given us some souveniers... you get the idea."
    Ky "Hemos estado ocupadas acondicionando este lugar. Los chicos de las torres nos han regalado algunos recuerdos... ya te haces una idea."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2757
translate spanish d14e_e821056c:

    # Ky "These quarters at least feel a bit closer to home, now."
    Ky "Al menos estos cuartos se sienten un poco más cercanos a casa ahora."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2759
translate spanish d14e_9421daad:

    # Ky "We're not giving free handouts to the motherfuckers who work here, but we're not squeezing their last drops either."
    Ky "No estamos dando limosna gratis a estos hijos de puta que trabajan aquí, pero tampoco les estamos exprimiendo hasta la última gota."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2760
translate spanish d14e_c424e14d:

    # Ky "The workers started noticing it, and they've been reaching out with ways to improve our mutual situation."
    Ky "Los trabajadores empezaron a notarlo, y se han acercado proponiendo formas de mejorar nuestra situación mutua."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2761
translate spanish d14e_70d61322:

    # Ky "There's even some trading going on..."
    Ky "Incluso hay algo de comercio..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2762
translate spanish d14e_2e875526:

    # Ky "{i}*sigh*{/i} I thought I'd complain... but the food... it's good grub."
    Ky "{i}*suspirando*{/i} Pensé que me quejaría... pero la comida... es buena comida."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2763
translate spanish d14e_94c2e6de:

    # Ky "I never thought I had talent for more than tearing people's insides up and feeding them to them."
    Ky "Nunca pensé que tenía talento para algo más que desgarrar las entrañas de la gente y dárselas de comer."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2766
translate spanish d14e_383c0a59:

    # Ky "You know how to squeeze any last drop out of these people, I've got to give you that. Last thing that's missing is a shock collar policy, {i}*laughs*{/i}."
    Ky "Sabes cómo exprimir hasta la última gota de esta gente, tengo que reconocértelo. Lo único que falta es una norma de collar de choque, {i}*risas*{/i}."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2767
translate spanish d14e_482b1306:

    # Ky "Which brings me to our new stuff. People need to know their place, so they won't act up."
    Ky "Lo que me lleva a nuestro nuevo material. La gente necesita saber cuál es su lugar, para no portarse mal."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2769
translate spanish d14e_0b5b540a:

    # Ky "Quite the settlement we've got now, don't we? Desperate wastelanders doing our bidding, just so we don't turn them out to starve in the dunes."
    Ky "Menudo asentamiento tenemos ahora, ¿no? Páramos desesperados a nuestro servicio, sólo para que no los echemos a morir de hambre en las dunas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2770
translate spanish d14e_83e16b31:

    # Ky "I mean, somebody has to be at the bottom of the foodchain and it sure as fuck isn't going to be me. But hey, at least they've got some new rights they didn't have before."
    Ky "Quiero decir, alguien tiene que estar en la parte inferior de la cadena alimentaria, y seguro que no voy a ser yo. Pero, al menos, tienen algunos nuevos derechos que antes no tenían."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2771
translate spanish d14e_7ece325c:

    # Ky "Still... people need to know their place, so they won't act up."
    Ky "Aún así... la gente necesita conocer su lugar, para no portarse mal."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2773
translate spanish d14e_aff7f692:

    # Ky "I feel like the new decor will help making them think twice before acting up when they enter this room."
    Ky "Siento que la nueva decoración hará que piensen dos veces antes de portarse mal cuando entren en esta habitación."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2774
translate spanish d14e_556457ab:

    # Ky "Other than that... my guys started forming small raiding parties again."
    Ky "Aparte de eso... mis chicos han vuelto a formar pequeñas partidas de asalto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2775
translate spanish d14e_fcad1a41:

    # Ky "Not going to lie, I don't mind not being on the frontline for once. This place ain't so bad. I could get used to this."
    Ky "No te voy a mentir, no me importa no estar en primera línea por una vez. Este lugar no está tan mal. Podría acostumbrarme a esto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2782
translate spanish d14e_56125150:

    # Ky "Also, you've got to change your outfit. That fine city shit won't get you any respect on this bridge."
    Ky "Además, debes cambiar tu vestuario. Esa ropa elegante de la ciudad no te ganará ningún respeto en este puente."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2789
translate spanish d14e_0dc8e5ee:

    # Z "{i}*laughs*{/i} Alright. Show me what you got."
    Z "{i}*risas*{/i} Está bien. Muéstrame lo que tienes."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2796
translate spanish d14e_bc0fd6f4:

    # "She looks down, pointing you towards the bed next to you..."
    "Ella mira hacia abajo, señalándote la cama de al lado..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2799
translate spanish d14e_156872ad:

    # "A crate lies under it, full of clothes, you imagine."
    "Debajo hay un cajón, lleno de ropa, te imaginas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2800
translate spanish d14e_6a68284d:

    # Ky "Try... I want to see you wearing it."
    Ky "Prueba... Quiero verte llevándolo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2803
translate spanish d14e_d2db97b2:

    # "Some minutes later..."
    "Unos minutos más tarde..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2806
translate spanish d14e_10769b45:

    # Z "No shirt, huh. You guys like to fight naked?"
    Z "Sin camiseta, eh. ¿Os gusta luchar desnudas?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2807
translate spanish d14e_f40a5dfa:

    # Ky "Don't worry about that, sweetie... I've got some armor prepared for us."
    Ky "No te preocupes por eso, cariño... Tengo preparada una armadura para nosotros."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2810
translate spanish d14e_026e83de:

    # Zt "Blades, bones and tribe insignia... not bad."
    Zt "Espadas, huesos e insignias tribales... no está mal."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2811
translate spanish d14e_30fa8cb9:

    # Ky "{i}*giggles*{/i}"
    Ky "{i}*risitas*{/i}"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2814
translate spanish d14e_95c1d008:

    # Ky "Lower your hands, show me everything..."
    Ky "Baja las manos, enséñamelo todo..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2815
translate spanish d14e_3e8fd50c:

    # Ky "Yeah... that's how I imagined it."
    Ky "Sí... así es como me lo imaginaba."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2821
translate spanish d14e_80558441:

    # As "What's happening, you imagined what..-"
    As "¿Qué está pasando, te imaginaste qué...?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2824
translate spanish d14e_8adb949c:

    # As "Whoa... Boss..."
    As "Vaya... Jefe..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2827
translate spanish d14e_c396eba2:

    # Ky "Raider [persistent.player_name]..."
    Ky "Asaltante [persistent.player_name]..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2828
translate spanish d14e_9f31d3ed:

    # Ky "Not bad at all... anyways... that's all I needed from you."
    Ky "No está nada mal... En fin... Esto es todo lo que necesitaba de ti."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2829
translate spanish d14e_431f3e43:

    # Ky "Welcome back to the overpass. Asha and I are glad to have you back."
    Ky "Bienvenido de nuevo al paso elevado. Asha y yo nos alegramos de que hayas vuelto."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2833
translate spanish d14e_9a1a7369:

    # Ky "Also... let me know when you want to have some fun again."
    Ky "Además... avísame cuando quieras divertirte de nuevo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2834
translate spanish d14e_6656b850:

    # Ky "I've grown to like your ways, old man..."
    Ky "Me han llegado a gustar tus maneras, viejo..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2848
translate spanish d14f_part_1_de31da6c:

    # Rai "I SAID DROP YOUR WEAPON, FREAK!"
    Rai "¡HE DICHO QUE SUELTES EL ARMA, MONSTRUO!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2849
translate spanish d14f_part_1_22916fbe:

    # C2 "Haheh, hahaheh. Me? Nooo!!"
    C2 "Jaheh, hahaheh. ¿Yo? ¡¡Nooo!!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2852
translate spanish d14f_part_1_edf34980:

    # C2 "I will not be the one who does so, no. No, no, no..."
    C2 "No seré yo quien lo haga, no. No, no, no..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2855
translate spanish d14f_part_1_49eb4b16:

    # C2 "YOUU will be the one dropping it, yes yes!"
    C2 "TUUU será el que la deje caer, ¡sí sí!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2858
translate spanish d14f_part_1_26a803bc:

    # C "..."
    C "..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2859
translate spanish d14f_part_1_a1bb6ac5:

    # C2 "She is one of yours, yes? So I will set an example."
    C2 "¿Ella es una de los tuyos, verdad? Así que pondré un ejemplo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2862
translate spanish d14f_part_1_35b28949:

    # C2 "Yes... I am the example. I am the ambassador."
    C2 "Sí... soy el ejemplo. Soy el embajador."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2865
translate spanish d14f_part_1_da589a50:

    # C2 "I am here to bring a message..."
    C2 "Estoy aquí para llevar un mensaje..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2868
translate spanish d14f_part_1_ece9230a:

    # C2 "THE LEGION IS COMING!!!"
    C2 "¡¡¡VIENE LA LEGIÓN!!!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2871
translate spanish d14f_part_1_ab6cde29:

    # Rai "We're going to put you down, freak! Last warning!"
    Rai "¡Vamos a acabar contigo, monstruo! ¡Último aviso!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2874
translate spanish d14f_part_1_7b57083a:

    # C2 "THEN SHOW ME WHAT YOU GOT, WASTELANDER!!"
    C2 "¡¡ENTONCES ENSÉÑAME LO QUE TIENES, BASURERO!!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2877
translate spanish d14f_part_1_85e45291:

    # C2 "SOON, THE LEGION WILL DEVOUR YOU ALL!!"
    C2 "¡¡PRONTO, LA LEGIÓN OS DEVORARÁ A TODOS!!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2878
translate spanish d14f_part_1_f0271ea5:

    # C2 "SEKHMET LIVES!!"
    C2 "¡¡SEKHMET VIVE!!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2881
translate spanish d14f_part_1_2b86999b:

    # C2 "WE ARE SEKHMET'S LEGION!!!"
    C2 "¡SOMOS LA LEGIÓN DE SEKHMET!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2882
translate spanish d14f_part_1_7e79b05e:

    # C2 "LET CHAOS REIGN!!"
    C2 "¡QUE REINE EL CAOS!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2889
translate spanish d14f_part_1_23a6a987:

    # C2 "...!"
    C2 "¡...!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2892
translate spanish d14f_part_1_3f208507:

    # Rai "I've got him. Open the gate!"
    Rai "Lo tengo. ¡Abre la puerta!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2895
translate spanish d14f_part_1_54bc956c:

    # C2 "Nghn..."
    C2 "Nghn..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2905
translate spanish d14f_part_2_d3fdf6e5:

    # Z "I heard something happened at the gate."
    Z "Escuché que algo pasó en la puerta."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2906
translate spanish d14f_part_2_7f54f756:

    # Z "Care to bring me up to speed?"
    Z "¿Te importaría ponerme al tanto?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2912
translate spanish d14f_part_2_f35d34d4:

    # Ky "Yes. One of our patrols got attacked. Only Nia surived, just about."
    Ky "Sí. Una de nuestras patrullas fue atacada. Solo Nia sobrevivió, por poco."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2918
translate spanish d14f_part_2_f87bc0c0:

    # Ky "The medic is seeing her now."
    Ky "La médica la está atendiendo ahora."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2919
translate spanish d14f_part_2_0f33bb33:

    # Ky "These legion assholes..."
    Ky "Esos cabrones de la legión..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2925
translate spanish d14f_part_2_dc6edba2:

    # Z "Legion? What legion?"
    Z "¿Legión? ¿Qué legión?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2931
translate spanish d14f_part_2_e43bac44:

    # Z "I've heard of tribes around these regions. But legions?!"
    Z "He oído hablar de tribus por estas regiones. ¡¿Pero legiones?!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2937
translate spanish d14f_part_2_2bb2f0c9:

    # Ky "That's what they go by. I didn't give 'em that name."
    Ky "Así es como se hacen llamar. Yo no les puse ese nombre."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2938
translate spanish d14f_part_2_82b981e4:

    # Ky "And no, they can't even be considered a tribe. A bunch of creepy fanatics, degenerates, if anything."
    Ky "Y no, ni siquiera se les puede considerar una tribu. Un montón de fanáticos espeluznantes, degenerados, si acaso."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2944
translate spanish d14f_part_2_70612053:

    # Ky "...Could be they moved, or their numbers have grown. I can't really explain this incursion in any other way."
    Ky "... Podría ser que se hayan mudado, o que sus números hayan crecido. No puedo explicar esta incursión de ninguna otra manera."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2954
translate spanish d14f_part_2_505399e8:

    # Zi "Alright. "
    Zi "De acuerdo."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2955
translate spanish d14f_part_2_036c2f57:

    # extend "What. "
    extend "¡¿Qué..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2956
translate spanish d14f_part_2_4294d053:

    # extend "The fuck. "
    extend "Diablos..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2957
translate spanish d14f_part_2_946844cf:

    # extend "Happened out there?!"
    extend "Pasó ahí afuera?!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2960
translate spanish d14f_part_2_3fcaeb2c:

    # Zi "What did they do to Nia?!?"
    Zi "¿¡¿Qué le hicieron a Nia?!?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2961
translate spanish d14f_part_2_557070f1:

    # Ky "Sekhmet's legion, Zion. They raided one of our patrols."
    Ky "La legión de Sekhmet, Zion. Asaltaron una de nuestras patrullas."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2964
translate spanish d14f_part_2_f5f78890:

    # Zi "Ngghrr..."
    Zi "Nghhrr..."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2966
translate spanish d14f_part_2_3e619e32:

    # Zi "FUCK!"
    Zi "¡JODER!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2972
translate spanish d14f_part_2_090675ed:

    # Zi "How is she? Tell me she survived!"
    Zi "¿Cómo está ella? ¡Dime que ha sobrevivido!"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2973
translate spanish d14f_part_2_66095383:

    # Zi "And where is the fucker who attacked her!?"
    Zi "¿Y dónde está el cabrón que la atacó?"

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2979
translate spanish d14f_part_2_26e3b055:

    # Ky "She's being treated, but she took a beating."
    Ky "La están tratando, pero recibió una paliza."

# game/scripts/day14.rpy:2980
translate spanish d14f_part_2_a2f2c823:

    # Ky "The fucker who did it is dead and burning. He actually marched her to the gate."
    Ky "El cabrón que lo hizo está muerto y ardiendo. De hecho, la obligó a caminar hasta la puerta."

